<template>
  <v-card>
    <v-container>
      <v-row>
        <v-col>
          <v-toolbar dark>
            <v-toolbar-title>Criar</v-toolbar-title>
            <v-spacer></v-spacer>
            <v-card-actions>
              <v-spacer></v-spacer>
              <v-btn class="m" @click="submit">
                <v-icon class="mr-3">mdi-feature-search-outline</v-icon>Search
              </v-btn>
            </v-card-actions>
          </v-toolbar>
        </v-col>
      </v-row>
      <v-row>
        <v-spacer></v-spacer>
        <v-col cols="12" sm="6" md="6" lg="5">
          <v-text-field 
            v-model="name"
            :error-messages="nameErrors"
            label="Nome"
            required
            @input="$v.name.$touch()"
            @blur="$v.name.$touch()">  
          </v-text-field>
        </v-col>
        <v-col cols="12" sm="6" md="6" lg="5">
          <v-text-field 
            v-model="local"
            :error-messages="localErrors"
            label="Em"
            required
            @input="$v.local.$touch()"
            @blur="$v.local.$touch()">  
          </v-text-field>
        </v-col>
        <v-spacer></v-spacer>
      </v-row>
    </v-container>
  </v-card>
</template>


<script>
import { validationMixin } from "vuelidate";
import { required } from "vuelidate/lib/validators";

export default {
  mixins: [validationMixin],
  validations: {
    name: { required },
    local: { required }
  },
  name:"searchArea",
  data: () => ({
    name: "",
    local: ""
  }),

  computed: {
    nameErrors() {
      const errors = [];
      if (!this.$v.name.$dirty) return errors;
      !this.$v.name.required && errors.push("Name is required.");
      return errors;
    },
    localErrors() {
      const errors = [];
      if (!this.$v.local.$dirty) return errors;
      !this.$v.local.required && errors.push("Local is required.");
      return errors;
    }
  },

  methods: {
    submit() {
      this.$v.$touch();
    }
  }
};
</script>
